parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the key to become stuck in the ignition, making it difficult or impossible to start or turn off the engine, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key becomes stuck in the ignition
the key is difficult to remove from the ignition
the ignition switch fails to turn off
the vehicle stalls or fails to start

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the ignition switch fails to turn off
the key becomes stuck in the ignition

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Recurring Ignition Switch Failure after Recall Repair
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch to be properly repaired during a recall can cause the same issues to recur, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key becomes stuck in the ignition
the ignition switch fails to turn off
the vehicle stalls or fails to start
despite previous repairs under a recall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of power steering can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially at low speeds.
symptoms: The power steering warning light illuminates
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle loses power steering while driving
the power steering comes back on after restarting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering shaft can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially at low speeds.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle loses power steering while driving
the steering shaft needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition Switch and Power Steering Recall Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch and power steering can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power steering, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The key gets stuck in the ignition switch
the power steering warning light illuminates
the vehicle loses power steering while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to safety risks, especially in cold weather conditions.
Failure of the timing chain or belt can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potential safety risks.
Failure of the cooling system can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage and potential safety risks.
Failure of the electrical system can cause various issues, including stalling, loss of power, and difficulty starting the vehicle.
Failure of the air conditioning system can cause discomfort and distraction while driving.
